						               													<description>Ordleg (&amp;quot;Word Play&amp;quot; in English) is a word dice game with game play the same as Ad-Lib Crossword Cubes. On your turn, you roll the 15 letter dice and arrange them into a crossword puzzle structure within the one minute time limit. Your score is based on the value of letters used. The player with the highest cumulative score after 10 rounds wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Two dice have one blank side. The game comes with two sheets of blank stickers so that you can cover these blank sides (or any other side of any die) and change the letter distribution to suit your preferred language.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Although the game comes with rules for 20 languages, including Greek and Russian, the game uses only the Latin alphabet. However, it comes with 100 blank stickers, enough to cover the sides of all 15 dice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
